    {%- assign faqs = 'How much syrup per snow cone?|Most people use 2-3 oz per snow cone for a vivid color and full-on flavor. For lighter taste, start with 1 oz and add more.;;Do I need a snow cone machine?|Nope! Any shaved or crushed ice works. A snow cone machine gives you that classic fluffy texture but a sturdy blender pulses on crushed ice work great too.;;What can I make besides snow cones?|Slushies, ice pops, italian sodas, milkshakes, smoothies, cocktails, mocktails. Anything cold + sweet.;;Is the syrup ready to use?|Yes. No mixing, no diluting. Pour directly from the bottle onto ice.;;How long does an open bottle last?|Sealed bottles keep up to 12 months at room temp. Once opened, store cool/dark and use within 6 months for best flavor.;;Is it kosher? Gluten free?|Yes — kosher certified, gluten free, dairy free, non-GMO.;;How fast do you ship?|Orders ship in 1 business day from our New Jersey warehouse. Flat-rate $5.99 shipping, free over $34.;;What if I do not love it?|30-day taste guarantee. Email us and we will refund, replace, or credit — your call.' | split: ';;' -%}
